just_use stack_type.go

# label: ELEGANT
# role: encodes domain knowledge

"The most important function of the game": GetStackType classifies a card
group as Incomplete / Bogus / Dup / Set / PureRun / RedBlackRun.

Wrapping arithmetic: Successor(K)=A, Predecessor(A)=K, so K-A-2 is a
valid run. This is a LynRummy house rule, not standard rummy.

Chosen representation: `type StackType string` for cheap debuggability at
the cost of compile-time exhaustiveness (Elm's sum type gets exhaustive
checks, Go's string aliases don't). Tradeoff taken deliberately.
